I beseech sweet Iesus, to giue grace to euery one
that offendeth in this sort, to see, repent, and get
pardon of their faults past, and light of true Fayth
in tyme to come; for obtayning whereof they
had need to pray to God for it, and with a great
desire to seeke after it, and with humility to submit
their will and Iudgment to those whom God
hath appointed to teach it; To wit, such Doctours
and Pastours as by a visible continuall succession,
haue without change brought it from christ
and his Apostles, euen vntill these our dayes; and
shall by a like succession carry it along, euen vntill
the end of world. The which succession not being
found in any other church, differing in doctrine from
